On November 14, 2001, SCE filed Advice 1586-E with the Commission.

Title:
Establishment of the Procurement Related Obligations Account and
Associated
Ratemaking Structure to be Implemented September 1, 2001 Consistent with
the October 2, 2001 Settlement Agreement Between the California Public
Utilities Commission and Southern California Edison Company

Purpose:
This advice filing establishes the ratemaking that is necessary to
implement a number of the regulatory components included in the October
2,
2001 Settlement Agreement between the Commission and SCE (Settlement
Agreement or Agreement).  The remaining sections of this filing include:
(1) Background; (2) Ratemaking Structure Effective September 1, 2001;
(3)
Calculation of Monthly Surplus; (4) Calculation of Monthly Recoverable
Costs; (5) Procurement Related Obligations Account (PROACT) Reporting;
and
(6) Settlement Rates.


To view other SCE advice letters, please click on the URL address below
and
select the Regulatory Info Center, Advice Letters.

http://www.sce.com/index.shtml

This notice is being sent to all interested parties of A.00-11-038,
A.00-03-047, and SCE's GO 96-A Service List.

